# Trivy ignore file — documented waiver for the ActiveMQ broker image.
#
# The 5.19.6→6.2.6 migration cleared FOUR of the five EOL CVEs that 5.19.6
# carried: Spring 6.2.x (bundled by 6.2.6) is past the affected ranges of
# CVE-2016-1000027 / CVE-2025-41249 / CVE-2024-38816 / CVE-2024-38819 — those
# are gone and are NOT listed here.
#
# One residual remains: jetty-http. ActiveMQ Classic 6.2.6 bundles Jetty
# 11.0.26, and this CVE is fixed only in Jetty 12 (12.0.33 / 12.1.7) — there is
# no Jetty 11.x fix (Jetty 11 is end-of-community-support). Moving to Jetty 12
# requires a future ActiveMQ line, tracked in the Upgrade Backlog. The vector
# (HTTP request smuggling via chunked-extension quoted-string parsing) requires
# a fronting proxy mis-parsing the console traffic; the demo console binds
# in-container and is not internet-exposed. Reviewed 2026-05-31; re-check when
# the ActiveMQ pin or its bundled Jetty version changes.
CVE-2026-2332
